A driver and passenger is considered lucky, after escaping from their vehicle, when it crashed into the Tugela River, Bergville in the early hours of Monday morning, 21 December. Chief Freddie Halgreen of the Okhahlamba Fire Department said that the two people made their way out of the vehicle, swam to the banks of the river and walked to the fire station, about a few meters away. “The two sustained no injuries and are extremely lucky,” said Halgreen. The cause of the accident is unknown at this stage.